  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**\r\nBUG\r\n\r\n**Kubernetes version** (use `kubectl version`):\r\nkubernetes/master\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\nn/a\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nevents were co-located in api server etcd\r\n\r\nthe controller-manager and node are spamming the node for different reasons and driving an excessive amount of traffic to our api-server.  this caused etcd snapshots to occur every 13s even with a 20k snapshot interval set.\r\n\r\nthe controller-manager can produce this problem in a simple manner by defining quota to 1 pod, and creating a replica-set whose target is 1000.  the replica set is burst in steps of 500 and each failed create is sent as a unique event.  in a short period of time, you get ~1300 PATCH event requests.  over enough replica-sets, this adds up.\r\n\r\nthe node is also prone to spam the server in the event of SyncFailed events.  for example, we had a pod that was in crash loop backoff for 3ds, and we got 21k FailedSync events.  over enough pods, this adds up.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe event recorder should protect against spam like this.\r\nThe replication controller should attempt burst in stages (1, 2, 3, 5, ...).\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it** (as minimally and precisely as possible):\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl metric | grep apiserver_request_latencies_summary_count | grep events\r\napiserver_request_latencies_summary_count{resource=\"events\",subresource=\"\",verb=\"PATCH\"} 11\r\napiserver_request_latencies_summary_count{resource=\"events\",subresource=\"\",verb=\"POST\"} 33\r\n$ kubectl create quota quota --hard=pods=1\r\n$ kubectl run nginx --image=nginx --replicas=100\r\n... wait a minute ...\r\n$ curl metric | grep apiserver_request_latencies_summary_count | grep events\r\napiserver_request_latencies_summary_count{resource=\"events\",subresource=\"\",verb=\"PATCH\"} 1300\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have a patch prepared that adds client side spam protection in the event recorder.\r\n\r\n```\r\napiserver_request_latencies_summary_count{resource=\"events\",subresource=\"\",verb=\"PATCH\"} 20\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know**:\r\nnope.\r\n",
